subSubSection.paragraph:
Kankuamo marquezi sp. n. inhabits Cuchilla San Lorenzo from Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta National Natural Park. Cuchilla San Lorenzo is located in its northwestern flank, in a gradient of altitude from 2000-2300 meters above sea level, in life zone of lower montane wet forest ( Espinal and Montenegro 1963 ). The Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta is an isolated mountain range separated from the Andes chain. The locations where the specimens were collected are covered mainly by shrubby plants of the families Arecaceae and Chrysobalanaceae (
Cuadrado-Pena 2005
), and inhabited by the snakes genus Atractus and frogs of the genera Atelopus , and the endemic species from Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta Ikakogi tayrona and Geobatrachus walkeri (MG personal observations).
